[
  {
    "text": "Just let go.",
    "source": "Ajahn Chah",
    "relatesTo": [
      "restless",
      "doubt",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "If you let go a little, you have a little peace.",
    "source": "Ajahn Chah",
    "relatesTo": [
      "sensual",
      "restless",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Do everything with a mind that lets go.",
    "source": "Ajahn Chah",
    "relatesTo": [
      "general",
      "view"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "The mind is just the mind. Thoughts are just thoughts.",
    "source": "Ajahn Chah",
    "relatesTo": [
      "illwill",
      "view",
      "restless"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Problems belong to the world. Suffering is in you.",
    "source": "Ajahn Chah",
    "relatesTo": [
      "illwill",
      "view"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Doubt is natural. Everyone starts with doubts.",
    "source": "Ajahn Chah",
    "relatesTo": [
      "doubt"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Sit. Sit again. That is all.",
    "source": "Ajahn Chah",
    "relatesTo": [
      "effort",
      "sloth"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "You are your own teacher. Looking outside is wrong.",
    "source": "Ajahn Chah",
    "relatesTo": [
      "doubt",
      "view"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Still, flowing water.",
    "source": "Ajahn Chah",
    "relatesTo": [
      "restless",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "The Dhamma has to be found by looking into your own mind.",
    "source": "Ajahn Chah",
    "relatesTo": [
      "doubt",
      "view"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Hatred does not cease by hatred. Only by love is it ended.",
    "source": "The Buddha (Dhp 5)",
    "relatesTo": [
      "illwill"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "You yourself must strive. The Buddhas only point the way.",
    "source": "The Buddha (Dhp 276)",
    "relatesTo": [
      "effort",
      "doubt",
      "sloth"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "All conditioned things are impermanent.",
    "source": "The Buddha (Dhp 277)",
    "relatesTo": [
      "general",
      "view",
      "sensual"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Mind precedes all things. Mind is their chief.",
    "source": "The Buddha (Dhp 1)",
    "relatesTo": [
      "view",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Health is the greatest gift, contentment the greatest wealth.",
    "source": "The Buddha (Dhp 204)",
    "relatesTo": [
      "sensual"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Come and see.",
    "source": "The Buddha (Ehipassiko formula)",
    "relatesTo": [
      "doubt",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "One thing I teach: suffering, and the end of suffering.",
    "source": "The Buddha (MN 22)",
    "relatesTo": [
      "general",
      "view"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Be islands unto yourselves. Take refuge in no other.",
    "source": "The Buddha (DN 16)",
    "relatesTo": [
      "doubt",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "As the ocean has one taste — salt — the dhamma has one taste: liberation.",
    "source": "The Buddha (Ud 5.5)",
    "relatesTo": [
      "view",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Better than a thousand useless words is one word that brings peace.",
    "source": "The Buddha (Dhp 100)",
    "relatesTo": [
      "restless",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Peace is every step.",
    "source": "Thich Nhat Hanh",
    "relatesTo": [
      "restless",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Smile, breathe, and go slowly.",
    "source": "Thich Nhat Hanh",
    "relatesTo": [
      "restless",
      "illwill"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Feelings come and go like clouds in a windy sky.",
    "source": "Thich Nhat Hanh",
    "relatesTo": [
      "illwill",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Drink your tea slowly and reverently.",
    "source": "Thich Nhat Hanh",
    "relatesTo": [
      "sensual",
      "restless"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "My religion is kindness.",
    "source": "HH the Dalai Lama",
    "relatesTo": [
      "illwill",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Happiness is not ready-made. It comes from your own actions.",
    "source": "HH the Dalai Lama",
    "relatesTo": [
      "effort",
      "sloth",
      "general"
    ]
  },
  {
    "text": "Be kind whenever possible. It is always possible.",
    "source": "HH the Dalai Lama",
    "relatesTo": [
      "illwill"
    ]
  }
]
